text: what is the cleanest way to parse a date time string that has micros and nanos?  E.g. "2019-03-30T00:00:00.000123456" ?  DateTime seems to only go up to millis

text: Can we cross post this publicly to <https://discourse.julialang.org|Discourse> for further visibility? React with :bridge: on the message above to approve. <https://github.com/JuliaCommunity/SlackBridge/blob/main/README.md#faq|More info here>

```julia> one, two = split(s, '.')
2-element Vector{SubString{String}}:
 "2019-03-30T00:00:00"
 "000123456"

julia> DateTime(one), Nanosecond(two)
(DateTime("2019-03-30T00:00:00"), Nanosecond(123456))```
you will have to do something like this because DateTime doesn't support nano second I think
